<headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 14 at 4:25AM EDT  by NWS Albany</headline>
<description>...Very heavy snowfall expected through 7 AM with rates of 2
inches per hour or greater...
A broad band of heavy snow is expanding north from the eastern
Catskills, mid Hudson Valley, central Taconics and Berkshires. The
heavy snow will expand across the Schoharie Valley, Capital
Region, Saratoga Region to Rensselaer Plateau and southern VT
through 7 AM.
Snowfall rates exceeding 2 inches per hour can be expected with
snowfall totals by 7 AM exceeding 6 inches in the Hudson Valley
and over a foot in higher elevations. Travel will be very
difficult through this morning.</description>
